---
title: Wasabi Lime Salmon over Soy-Simmered Rice with Baby Bok Choy
description: It’s not often that you see wasabi outside of a sushi plate. But the sinus-clearing condiment can be used to add an unexpected lift to all sorts of dishes—like this meal of pan-seared salmon and bok choy over soy sauce–infused rice, which is taken from basic to bold with a wasabi lime dressing. Just be sure to add the paste to taste; you want it to have a kick, not a wallop.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/wasabi-lime-salmon-1e63bfb0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/wasabi-lime-salmon-b5ffbbc6.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 860 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/wasabi-lime-salmon-592dcd7e99052d64f4604612
---

Bring @water{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @soy sauce{1%tsp} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered.

Wash and dry all produce. Cut off and discard root ends of @baby bok choy{2}, then separate into individual stalks. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Halve @lime{1}. Cut one half into wedges. Peel, then finely grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, a pinch of garlic, a pinch of ginger, and @wasabi paste{1%tsp} (to taste—start with a pinch and go up from there). Stir in @water{2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add more water as needed to give dressing a drizzly consistency. Just be sure to add the paste to taste; you want it to have a kick, not a wallop.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites, remaining garlic, and remaining ginger. Cook, tossing, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add bok choy and @water{1%tbsp}. Cook, tossing, until leaves wilt, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove mixture from pan and set aside, covering with #aluminum foil{} to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Season @skin-on salmon{12%oz} all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan skin-side down. Cook until skin is crisp and browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Lower heat to medium and flip salmon. Cook until opaque throughout, another ~{3-4%minutes}.

Divide rice between plates. Top with bok choy and salmon. Drizzle with dressing and garnish with scallion greens. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing.